16/04/2008
WASHINGTON, United States -- President George W. Bush has written to Macedonian counterpart Branko Crvenkovski and Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski, reiterating Washington's resolve to help find a mutually acceptable solution to the name dispute between Macedonia and Greece.
He also vowed support for Macedonia's efforts to join NATO, according to Macedonian media reports Wednesday (April 16th).
Separately, US State Department deputy spokesman Tom Casey stressed on Monday that the name dispute process continues under UN auspices and that the United States is not trying to take it over.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 16/04/08;
Sitel, Makfax - 15/04/08)
